The Woman I Wanted to Be

mainText: Mar 8 International Womens Day! Hi lovies! I wanted to share some books written by women that inspire and encourage me in my journey to becoming the woman I aspire to be. I have learned so much from all these trailblazing women and I know they will inspire you too. Educating yourself on other people‚Äôs experiences and showing compassion towards them is how barriers and stereotypes are broken down. We have more in common then we know. It is important when talking about supporting our fellow badass babes that we ensure we are including women of all races, abilities, sexual orientation, classes, and religious beliefs. We will continue to fight for our joint goals and we will not be underestimated. Women are a force in this world that will not be tamed. We Should all be Feminists by Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie Men Explain Things to Me by Rebecca Solnit Heart Talk by Cleo Wade the sun and her flowers by Rupi Kaur Bloom for Yourself by April Green The Bluest Eye by Toni Morrison You Are A Badass by Jen Sincero The Feminine Mystique by Betty Friedan Bringing Up Bebe by Pamela Druckerman It‚Äôs Messy by Amanda deCadenet The Crossroads of Should and Must by Elle Luna The Woman I Wanted to Be by Diane Von Furstenberg Diana In Her Words by Andrew Morton The New Jim Crow by Michelle Alexander Pivot by Jenny Blake Grace, A Memoir by Grace Coddington Gio Graphy by Giovanna Battaglia In Progress by Jessica Hische Together We Rise She Persisted by Time Magazine Audrey Hepburn by Life Magazine Darling Magazine Aileen Subscribe to my latest looks!
